**Done.** Created `src/pages/AITutorChat.tsx` (681 lines) and added route to `src/components/Layout.tsx`.

### What was built

`src/pages/AITutorChat.tsx` — full AI Tutor chat page with:

- **Chat interface** — scrollable message list, textarea input with Enter/Shift+Enter, send button with loading state
- **ModeSelector** integrated at the top (reuses existing `ModeSelector` component)
- **Language toggle** (EN / VI / Both) stored via `LocalTutorStorage.patchPreferences`
- **Local chat history** via `LocalTutorStorage` (Dexie/IndexedDB) — sessions auto-created per mode, messages persisted on send
- **Simulated AI response generator** — detects topics (grammar, vocabulary, speaking, writing, reading, listening, IELTS, planning, environment, education, technology, etc.) and generates contextual responses in English, Vietnamese, or both
- **Mode-specific greetings and prompts** displayed on empty session
- **Quick actions** row (Teach Me, Quiz Me, Correct Me, Explain Simply, Examples, Practice)
- **Suggested action buttons** on each assistant message
- **Suggested prompts** on empty state (teach grammar, environment vocabulary, writing tips, speaking practice)
- **Clear chat** button
- **Error/loading/retry** states
- Route: `/tutor` with nav item "AI Tutor" in sidebar

### Validation

- TypeScript compiles clean (`tsc --noEmit` → no errors)
- All 77 existing tests pass (`vitest run` → 4 suites, 77 tests, all passed)
